The paper proposes a new network architecture for learning on graphs, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The proposed architecture is applied to the inductive node classification problem and the traffic speed forecasting problem, which are both related to computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of a Graph Gated Recurrent Unit (GGRU), which is a type of neural network commonly used in natural language processing and sequential data analysis (cs.NE).
